cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be2 {This is a very old and solid line. White's
idea is to complete the development first and then start some active play in
the center or on the kingside according to what Black does.} Nf6 {This is my
recommended move order.} (6... a6 7. Nxc6 $5 bxc6 {This used to be considered
sufficient to equalize but it's not the case anymore.} (7... Qxc6 8. O-O b5 (
8... Bc5) 9. Bf3 Bb7 10. Bf4 $14 {Black's position is unpleasant.}) (7... dxc6
8. O-O e5 9. f4 Bd6 10. f5 b5 11. Qd3 Nf6 12. Qg3 $14) 8. Qd3 (8. O-O Nf6 9. f4
d5 10. e5 Nd7 11. Na4 (11. Kh1 Be7) 11... Nb6 $11) (8. Qd4 d5 9. exd5 cxd5 10.
Bf4 Qc5 11. Qxc5 Bxc5 12. Na4 Ba7 13. c4 Bd7 14. Nc3 dxc4 15. Bxc4 a5 $13) 8...
d5 (8... Bd6 9. Be3 Nf6 {Hovhannisyan - Movsesian, Reykjavik 2019} 10. g4 $5
