) 9. e5 axb5 10. exf6 b4 (10... gxf6 11. Nxb5 $36 {Although Black is a pawn up,
Black's position is unpleasant because of the damaged kingside pawn structure
and White's strong knight on b5.}) 11. fxg7 Bxg7 12. Nb5 {This position drew a
lot of attention recently and White has excellent statistics but I don't
believe it's that dangerous to Black, however, Black needs to be accurate in
any case.} d5 13. O-O O-O 14. Bd3 (14. Kh1 Bd7 15. Rf3 Qd8 16. Rh3 h6 17. Rg3
